HEADWORD: Britannia
<hw>Bri*tan"ni*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>Britannia</ets> Great Britain.]</ety> <def>A white-metal alloy of
tin, antimony, bismuth, copper, etc. It somewhat resembles silver, and
is used for table ware. Called also <altname>Britannia
metal</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

